  "instructions": [
    "preheat oven to 140c (284f)",
    "in a large bowl, combine tomatoes, sugar, salt, and minced garlic",
    "mix until the tomatoes release their juices and the mixture is well combined",
    "transfer the mixture to a large, oven-safe pot or Dutch oven",
    "add the sweetened condensed milk, balsamic vinegar, and olive oil to the pot",
    "stir until the sweetened condensed milk is well combined with the tomato mixture",
    "cover the pot with a lid and transfer to the preheated oven",
    "bake for 2 hours, stirring every 30 minutes",
    "remove the pot from the oven and let it cool slightly",
    "serve the sweet, gooey tomato confit warm, garnished with chopped fresh herbs if desired",
    "note: this dish can be made ahead and refrigerated or frozen for later use"
